maintext:
Burglars take money from town of Middleton auto parts store, sheriff’s office says
A town of Middleton auto parts store was burglarized early Wednesday morning, the Sheriff’s Office said.
Deputies went to a O’Reilly Auto Parts store, 6902 Watts Road at about 1:50 a.m. because of an alarm, said Dane County Sheriff’s Office spokeswoman Elise Schaffer.
She said deputies found a damaged front door, adding that an undisclosed amount of cash was taken.
Suspect descriptions weren’t provided.
